wiki.summary: "Dangerous Woman" is a song recorded by American singer Ariana Grande, serving as the lead single for her third studio album of the same name (2016). It was written by Johan Carlsson, Ross Golan and Max Martin, with Martin and Carlsson both serving as record and vocal producers. The song was first released along with the pre-order of the album on iTunes Store on March 11, 2016 and was sent to US contemporary hit and rhythmic radio on March 15, 2016. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Dangerous Woman" is a song recorded by American singer Ariana Grande, serving as the lead single for her third studio album of the same name (2016). It was written by Johan Carlsson, Ross Golan and Max Martin, with Martin and Carlsson both serving as record and vocal producers. The song was first released along with the pre-order of the album on iTunes Store on March 11, 2016 and was sent to US contemporary hit and rhythmic radio on March 15, 2016. "Dangerous Woman" is a midtempo pop and R&B song with an arena rock chorus and a guitar solo during its bridge. Read more on Last.fm.
